      "content": "The \"neutral framework\" approach is more legitimate because it protects the core democratic principle that no individual should be forced to violate their conscience, whereas allowing exemptions to laws like anti-discrimination statutes would create a system where some citizens are legally bound to harm others based on their beliefs. If the state permits religious groups to opt-out of universal mandates, it effectively grants them a privileged status that undermines the equal protection guaranteed to all citizens. A healthy democracy requires a unified legal baseline that prevents the state from becoming a tool of coercion, ensuring that the freedom of conscience is not conditional on agreeing to ignore the rights of others.",
